history.text: Hi! Have you seen The Blind Side?
Yes, I have!
I rather liked it.
Me, too. I enjoyed it!
How about you?
Sorry, sent it too late.
It surprised me how much I enjoyed Sandra Bullock in it. I'm not usually a fan.
Really? I tend to like Sandra Bullock, though I don't tend to watch dramas.
I do. And I usually like biopics, too. Somethines the can be overly sentimental, I think. But this one had a really strong story.
I think so, too. It was good story.
Do you like sports movies?
Not usually. There are a few standouts though and this is one of them.
What was your favorite scene?
I really enjoyed when Big Mike met S.J. They have really good dynamic together.
How about you?
Big Mike and SJ together melt my heart! I love when he stops the airbag with his bare arm.
Big Mike IS such a strong guy, hence being so good in football.
It's been a while since I saw the movie though and I had forgotten that Tim McGraw was SJ's dad.
I'm not so familiar with Tim McGraw, but I did enjoy him acting as a father.
It was a good role. He was supportive of his wife brining this stranger into their home to live.

I wonder where Leigh Anne learned to be comfortable with a such a strong kid who has issues (academically and with his family) and is clearly in a different social class
, enough to welcome him into her home.
I know that this is based on a true story, but it still seems rather unusual to me.
She seemed to me to be a 'nurturer.' Especially when she explains to Big Mike that he has to 'protect' his quarterback.
She may have told him to protect others, but she is the lineman in his life, it seems.
Oh, that's a great way to put it!
Haha, thanks :)
At least Big Mike is confused about Leigh Anne's motivations, too.
It's sad that he still wants to make things work with his biological mom, even after all he's been through.
Oh yes, that's so sad. You never forget your mama though.
In the end though, he realizes Tuohy family is his family
After making sure that he gets better grades and gets into college, it makes sense that he sees the people who did so much for him as family.
And I liked that he literally fought people involved in his past to protect his (new) family, too.
What did you think of the ratings for this movie?
I'm surprised they aren't higher, actually.
69% seems low.
Don't you think?
I think maybe the story seems a little strange to critics, though I believe all the actors did a great job. I think it could have been scored higher if they thought about the actors more.
Thanks for chatting!
